## Problem 2: No Self-Healing

### 🔴 The Real-World Scenario

It's 3 AM. Your Node.js app crashes due to an unhandled promise rejection. PM2 tries to restart it but hits a memory leak and keeps crashing. Your on-call engineer gets paged. By the time they respond, SSH, and debug — **47 minutes of downtime** has passed.

```
EC2 Failure Timeline:
[App crashes at 03:00] → [CloudWatch alarm: 3 min delay] → [SNS → PagerDuty: 1 min]
→ [Engineer wakes: 10 min] → [SSH login + debug: 20 min]
→ [Fix + restart: 13 min]
= 47 minutes downtime
```

### 🟡 EC2 "Fix" Attempt

You add CloudWatch alarms + Lambda to restart instances. Now you've built a mini-orchestration system. It breaks in weird edge cases, and you're maintaining it forever.

### 🟢 How Kubernetes Fixes It

Kubernetes has **liveness probes** and **restartPolicy** built in. It watches every pod continuously and restarts failed containers **within seconds** — no human needed.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as App Pod
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet (node agent)
    participant API as K8s API Server
    participant Sched as Scheduler

    App->>App: Process crashes (OOMKilled)
    Kubelet->>App: Liveness probe fails (HTTP 500)
    Kubelet->>API: Report pod unhealthy
    API->>Kubelet: Restart container (backoff: 10s)
    Kubelet->>App: New container starts
    Note over App: 🟢 Back online in ~10 seconds
    alt Pod keeps crashing
        API->>Sched: Reschedule to different node
        Sched->>App: Pod running on healthy node
    end
```

```yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: ecommerce-api
spec:
  replicas: 3
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: api
        image: ecommerce-api:v2.1
        livenessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /health
            port: 3000
          initialDelaySeconds: 10
          periodSeconds: 5
          failureThreshold: 3
        readinessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /ready
            port: 3000
          periodSeconds: 5
```

> ✅ **Result:** App restarts in **~10 seconds automatically**. Your engineer sleeps. SLA maintained.

