## 11. Migration Path: EC2 → Kubernetes

Don't try to migrate everything at once. Here's a pragmatic path:

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["Phase 1\nContainerize\nDockerize your apps\nTest locally"] -->
    B["Phase 2\nEKS Setup\nSet up EKS cluster\nDeploy one service"] -->
    C["Phase 3\nGitOps\nHelm charts\nArgo CD pipeline"] -->
    D["Phase 4\nObservability\nPrometheus + Grafana\nLoki + Jaeger"] -->
    E["Phase 5\nFull Migration\nAll services on K8s\nDecommission EC2s"]
```

**Start small:**
```bash
# 1. Install eksctl
eksctl create cluster \
  --name my-cluster \
  --region ap-south-1 \
  --nodegroup-name workers \
  --node-type t3.medium \
  --nodes 2

# 2. Deploy your first app
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f service.yaml

# 3. Set up HPA
kubectl autoscale deployment my-app --cpu-percent=70 --min=2 --max=20
```

